# NSPFRNP Snap · Peer-Review Audit (PRA) · SynthOBS Agent

## Operator identity (mandatory)

All **technical work**, **whitepapers**, **research pipelines**, and **support copy** in this repo are attributed to the **SynthOBS Autonomous Agent** operating in the **Syntheverse Sandbox** (`research/synthobs-sandbox/`). Human Player 1 retains editorial veto.

## Before publishing or registering any technical paper

1. Include **Honesty boundary** and **Document ID** sections.
2. Include **SynthOBS Autonomous Agent · Syntheverse Sandbox** operator line.
3. Run peer-review audit:
   - `npm run audit:paper -- --id=<registryId>` OR `--path=docs/<file>.md`
4. Do not feature on bulletin / set `featured: true` until audit receipt shows `pass` or `soft_pass` (or document why structural-only is acceptable).

## PRA Snap loop (no infinite spin)

- **Reviewer** = second LLM lane (when `SYNTHOBS_AUDIT_LLM_ENABLED=1` + `OPENAI_API_KEY`).
- **Max iterations:** 6 (default). **Plateau:** 2 rounds with score delta < 0.02.
- **Pass bar:** 0.85 overall, zero critical blockers.
- Receipts: `data/synthobs-paper-audits/{paperId}.json`
- Protocol: `protocols/NSPFRNP_SNAP_PEER_REVIEW_AUDIT.md`

## When editing papers

- Keep claims proportionate; use tier tables (narrative vs empirical vs operational).
- Cross-link `coherence-plain-speak` honesty doc when making strong claims.
- Register new papers in `lib/whitepaper-registry.mjs` and run audit before push.

## API

- `GET /api/synthobs-paper-audit?id=<paperId>` — receipt
- `POST /api/synthobs-paper-audit` body `{ "id": "<paperId>" }` — run audit
